population.title: Hospitalized Patients with Primary Diagnosis of Heart Failure
population.description: This cohort includes patients hospitalized with a primary discharge diagnosis of heart failure. The primary discharge diagnosis refers to the main clinical condition responsible for the hospital admission.

features.name: smoking_status_smoker_last
features.description: Determines if the patient is currently smoking. A patient is considered a current smoker if their last recorded smoking status is one of the following: 'Current every day smoker,' 'Current some day smoker,' 'Smoker, current status unknown,' 'Current heavy tobacco smoker,' or 'Current light tobacco smoker' and either has no recorded end date or the end date is after the reference time point. If the last recorded status is 'Former smoker' and it has an end date before the reference time point, the patient is considered a current smoker. If the status is 'Unknown if ever smoked,' the result is empty; otherwise, the patient is considered a non-smoker.

features.name: smoking_status_formerSmoker_last
features.description: Whether the patient smoked within 1 year prior to the admission end.The patient is considered to have smoked if their most recent smoking status is 'Current every day smoker,' 'Current some day smoker,' 'Smoker, current status unknown,' 'Current heavy tobacco smoker,' or 'Current light tobacco smoker' and either: 1. The recorded start date is within 365 days of the reference time point, 2. There is no recorded end date, or 3. The recorded end date is within 365 days of the reference time point. If the last recorded status is 'Former smoker,' the patient is considered to have smoked in the past year if either the smoking start date is within 365 days of the reference time point or the smoking end date is before the reference time point. If the status is 'Unknown if ever smoked,' the result is empty; otherwise, the patient is considered a non-smoker.

features.description: Total duration of smoking in days.
generatedDescription: for Filter the active smoking status.
